# State Management Patterns

## One Bloc per feature, many actions

Each async action owns a `BlocStatus` field on the state — not its own Bloc.
State classes have `copyWith` + value equality; events are a `sealed`/`final`
class hierarchy. Concurrency via `bloc_concurrency`: stream subscriptions →
`restartable()`, pull-to-refresh / one-shot mutations → `droppable()`.

## BlocStatus — per-action status

`lib/core/state/bloc_status.dart` models `initial / loading / success / empty /
failure`. Emit `BlocStatus.empty()` when a loaded list is empty so the UI shows
an empty illustration. Wrap errors as `BlocStatus.failure(AppException.from(err,
st))`.

```dart
emit(state.copyWith(loadStatus: const BlocStatus.loading()));
await emit.forEach(
  _repo.watchLibrary(),
  onData: (list) => state.copyWith(
    manga: list,
    loadStatus: list.isEmpty ? const BlocStatus.empty() : const BlocStatus.success(),
  ),
  onError: (e, st) =>
      state.copyWith(loadStatus: BlocStatus.failure(AppException.from(e, st))),
);
```

## Rendering — prefer StatusBuilder

```dart
StatusBuilder<LibraryBloc, LibraryState>(
  statusSelector: (s) => s.loadStatus,
  emptyMessage: 'library.empty'.tr(),
  onSuccess: (context) => const LibraryGrid(),
)
```

Drop to `BlocBuilder` only for multi-status UI or when the builder needs state
data. Use `BlocSelector`/`buildWhen` to keep rebuilds tight.

## Local widget state — ValueNotifier

Toggles, search fields, page indices, progress → `ValueNotifier` +
`ValueListenableBuilder`; merge several with
`Listenable.merge([...])` in a `ListenableBuilder`. Never `setState`. Always
`dispose()` notifiers/controllers.
